rComments: Not factually aware of the different Indigenous cultures myself, I went to her office asking for help. This improved my comprehension and participation levels immensely. Suzack sets a limited amount of time for each of her students that may frustrate some--but she will genuinely guide you if you show her that you've done the readings and research.

Not accessibility friendly, syllabus requires in person appointments or office hrs to ask for accommodation needs. Emails with other profs with attached accommodation letter normally suffices. Lectures are not clear and doesn't allow outside sources in essays. She doesn't cover any information on Indigenous symbolism or culture & somehow expects it
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'So many papers', 'Participation matters']

rComments: Suzack has mandatory attendence, and while you would hope there are exceptions to the matter, as in if you have gone through the nightmare of navigating accessibility services, accommodation letters and doctors notes - there are NO EXCEPTIONS. I missed two classes due to functional (dis)ability, and was given a preemptive C, risking an F. DROP.

I'm sure she's a very nice person, and she clearly knows what she's talking about, but Suzack is quite frankly not a great Prof. She's disorganized, unresponsive in email, and her lectures could not be more boring. Her assignments were confusing and unclear. The only good thing about the class was the syllabus.
Great prof.  Funny (or at least tried to be).  Chose great material for a tough subject.  Wasn't too hard of a marker.  Brought in a guest lecturer.  Variety of texts.

Amazing teacher, one of the best professors I've had at U of T. Eloquent lecturer who gives a clear sense of why what we're studying matters. Takes student contributions seriously and is very approachable after class/ in office hours. Gives thoughtful, helpful comments on assignments. I'd take any class Prof. Suzack taught.

Boring lecturer, to be honest repeats the same point throughout the whole semester in slightly different ways. Her marking is all over the place, expect average and random low marks. Also would avoid her soley for her testing methods
She is a great professor. Very engaging, easy to talk to, and she knows her stuff. Her classes were always inclusive, meaning that everyone got to participate and she took all our opinions seriously.

Amazing Professor! Absolute highlight of my entire undergraduate experience. Assignments and homework are manageable but you'll need to engage in class to pass. If you have concerns or you are confused, TALK. TO. HER.  Tough classes but really inspiring and challenging.
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader']

rComments: Wonderful, wonderful professor. One of the best at U of T. Possibly one of the smartest and most socially conscious people I've ever come into contact with.   Once you realize her voice sounds like Sandra Bullock's you won't be able to un-hear it.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Participation matters']

rComments: Prof. Suzack is one of the best profs I've ever had. She really pushes you to think more critically and to strengthen your skills. She is brilliant and makes you work for your grade. She is a fair marker and feedback is good.  Lectures are super interesting and she's quite funny. I would really recommend taking her class.
Excellent prof.  Articulate and helpful, but she does not cater to the lowest common denominator.  Definitely be on your a-game for her classes!
Avoid at all costs. Utterly unhelpful, not concise and too pedantic. Highly questionable sense of authority in class. Worst class ever.

AMAZING course, reading list is brilliant. I  dont usually enjoy English courses all that much because I find I'm not learning much that I can take with me beyond the classroom. This class has been the exception, and Prof. Suzack is wonderful.

Extremely random grading system.I'm a solid A student, ended up with a B. Not friendly during office hours. Felt like marks were a result of favouritism. Speak up and suck up in class and I am sure you'll do well!
